---
import DocsLayout from '../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="API Documentation" description="Generate and explore Swagger-based API docs">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">API Documentation</h1>

  <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">
    Cepress Generator can automatically generate Swagger (OpenAPI) documentation for your REST API.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Swagger UI</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">If enabled, you can visit the Swagger UI at:</p>

  <pre class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-md p-4 text-sm overflow-auto"><code>http://localhost:3000/api-docs</code></pre>

  <p class="mb-6">This provides a live, interactive view of all your endpoints, request/response types, and schemas.</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-6">How It Works</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
    <li>• Swagger config is located in <code>src/swagger.ts</code></li>
    <li>• Decorated route handlers automatically generate specs</li>
    <li>• You can customize descriptions, examples, and tags</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-12 mb-6">Disabling Swagger</h2>
  <p class="mb-4">You can disable Swagger during project setup or remove the related middleware from <code>src/index.ts</code>.</p>
</DocsLayout>
